## Note-management

The `note-management` skill (`skills/note-management/SKILL.md`) owns the unified directives store at `state/directives.json` — every "flag / don't flag" rule and every forward note.

Before surfacing any item, run:
```bash
python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py check "<text>" --scope <skill>
```

When {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} gives a forward note ("for tomorrow", "don't forget"):
```bash
python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py add --action remind --until <date> --match "<note>" --scope morning-brief --note "captured $(date +%F)"
```

Same turn, no waiting.
